• Strong aptitude for numbers and comfortable handling large volumes of data;
• Hands on experience in the execution of projects using data analytics and visualization software like SAS ,Tableau , PowerBI;
• Experienced in using database development tools like SQL, Hadoop;
• Adept at programming using Python, R and knowledgeable in data science concepts like machine learning, NLP (Natural Language Processing) and Business Application of Statistics;
• Strong interpersonal and communication skills.
Desired Skill-set:
• Certifications in data... analytics / business intelligence tools.
Responsibilities:
• Responsible for the design and development of holistic People analytics reports ;
• Extract large datasets from Human Resource (HR) Centers of Excellence;
• Collaborate with human resources and organizational partners to identify business objectives and pain points;
• Apply advanced data analysis techniques and transform HR data into actionable insights;
• Enhance intellectual analytical capabilities integrating current and new HR systems;
• Work hand in hand with stakeholders to enable data analytics based critical decision making;
• Keep abreast of the latest developments in data science and contribute to new data science studies.

